        Decode byte vector from stream.

        Any non null value found in stream is returned as the value part of an ITagValue object retrieved from the free pool of the given message.

        Note that this will never return an isNone() value - it will always return null instead.

      • setLogStream

        public void setLogStream(OutputStream logStream)
        Description copied from interface: IStopBitDecoder
        Associates an output stream with the decoder.

        If present, all bytes read from the decoder's input stream will be copied to this log stream.

        May be null - in which case no logging occurs (the default).

        Specified by:
        setLogStream in interface IStopBitDecoder
        Parameters:
        logStream - Output stream where input bytes are logged.
